The paper proposes a deep learning approach for relational databases, which is a topic closely related to database management systems (cs.DB). The proposed Equivariant Relational Layer (ERL) is a neural network layer that can be used for inductive and transductive reasoning in databases, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of ERL for natural language processing tasks, such as entity resolution and relation extraction, which is related to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the linear complexity of the proposed model, which suggests that it may be relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
